#! for all $i = 1 \dots m$.
#! The output is list of such morphisms $X_j: B_j \rightarrow C_j$ for $j=1\dots n$.
#! @Returns a list of morphisms $[X_1, \dots, X_n]$
#! @Arguments alpha, beta, gamma
